{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"C4 probe disposition: a live HTTP 429 could not be forced on demand, so ACLI's exact 429 exit code + whether it retries 429 internally remain unverified in production. Implementation is defensive: _rate_limit_backoff detects rate-limit markers in stderr (works regardless of exit code) and honors Retry-After only when present, else jittered exp backoff, all capped at 60s; _MAX_ATTEMPTS bounds attempts; terminal contract unchanged (CalledProcessError). If ACLI retries 429 internally, the Python backoff simply never triggers. See ADR 0036."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783539285302846001,"uuid":"2dcbea6a-3949-495d-b51a-b2d09d5d7ba3"}